<!-- WHAT WE DON'T DO -->
<div class="adv-section adv-principles">
  <div class="adv-section__inner">
    <div class="adv-section-label">How we work</div>
    <h2 class="adv-section-title">Editorial <em>principles</em></h2>

    <div class="adv-principles-grid">
      <div class="adv-principle">
        <div class="adv-principle-icon">✦</div>
        <h3 class="adv-principle-title">No disguised advertising</h3>
        <p class="adv-principle-text">All sponsored content is clearly labeled. Readers know when content is paid for. We believe transparency builds trust — and trust is the only thing that makes sponsorships worth anything.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="adv-principle">
        <div class="adv-principle-icon">✦</div>
        <h3 class="adv-principle-title">Editorial independence</h3>
        <p class="adv-principle-text">Kayla's opinions are not for sale. Sponsors can place content in this publication — they cannot purchase endorsements or direct editorial positions. The line is non-negotiable.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="adv-principle">
        <div class="adv-principle-icon">✦</div>
        <h3 class="adv-principle-title">Category fit required</h3>
        <p class="adv-principle-text">We only work with brands that make sense in this context — fintech, crypto, technology, books, policy organizations, professional services, and similar. We decline categories that conflict with the editorial voice.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="adv-principle">
        <div class="adv-principle-icon">✦</div>
        <h3 class="adv-principle-title">No political campaigns</h3>
        <p class="adv-principle-text">This site does not accept advertising from political campaigns, PACs, or partisan political organizations. The editorial content speaks for itself.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

